The paper focuses on the training of deep neural networks using backpropagation, which is a core topic in the field of neural networks and machine learning. The specific architecture discussed is convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the higher level logic and conceptual clarity of the backpropagation process, which could also place it in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
